title: Mission accomplished for Toundra Greenhouse - Quebec's largest greenhouse complex with year-round production officially inaugurated

description: [PR Newswire] - SAINT-FÉLICIEN, QC, Dec. 14, 2016 /CNW Telbec/ - Toundra Greenhouse management, accompanied by the Premier of Quebec and several officials and partners, officially inaugurated the greenhouse complex destined to become the largest in Quebec. Toundra Greenhouse is a cucumber-growing complex and four-phase project, which, upon completion, will have absorbed an investment of $100 million and created over 500 jobs. "For us, creating Toundra Greenhouse is an extraordinary accomplishment," said Toundra CEO Éric Dubé.
title: Mission accomplished for Toundra Greenhouse - Quebec's largest greenhouse complex with year-round production officially inaugurated
